$$2 = \log_{64^{\frac{1}{3}}}4^x = \frac{x \log_{4} 4}{\log_{4} 64^{\frac{1}{3}}} = \frac{x \log_{4} 4}{\frac{1}{3} \log_{4} 64} = \frac{3x}{\log_{4} 4}$$
$$\Rightarrow 2 \log_{4} 4 = 3x$$
$$\Rightarrow \frac{2}{\log_{4} 4} \log_{4} 4 = 3x$$
$$\Rightarrow 8 = 3x$$
$$\Rightarrow \boxed{x = 8/3}$$
